The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Telecom operators and handset manufacturers have asked the finance ministry to ensure that goods and services levy did not increase the burden of tax on the sector. The government plans to implement GST by April 2010. It will replace central and state levies, service tax, value-added tax and local levies.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: Credit card spending in the country has slumped by more than 12 per cent in the first five months of this fiscal to nearly Rs 24,427 crore as shoppers have decided against using their cards amid the ongoing economic slowdown.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 12: The government today notified its decision to double sugar purchase from millers for supply through ration shops in the 2009-10 season to protect the poor against high sweetener prices.                             
	 Mumbai, Oct. 12: Insurance regulator IRDA is considering whether to allow banks to tie-up with two-to-three insurance companies to sell their insurance products, a senior IRDA official said. Presently, banks cannot have agency tie-ups with more than one insurer.                             
	 Calcutta, Oct. 12: TVS Motor Company targets to take on market leader Bajaj over the next three years in the three-wheeler segment. The company entered this segment 14 months back with its autorickshaws.
                                                                                                                           
